---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Button from '../components/Button.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About — MakeBusinessShine"
  description="Wellington-based bilingual web studio run by a former QA engineer. Sites that work, in English and 中文."
>
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-[1100px] px-5 pb-12 pt-16 sm:px-6 sm:pt-24">
    <p class="font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-pounamu">About</p>
    <h1 class="mt-4 max-w-3xl text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-ink sm:text-5xl">
      I'm Henry. I make websites that pass their own tests.
    </h1>
  </section>

  <section class="mx-auto max-w-[1100px] px-5 pb-20 sm:px-6">
    <div class="grid gap-10 lg:grid-cols-[260px_1fr] lg:gap-12">
      <aside class="space-y-4">
        <div
          class="aspect-square w-full max-w-[260px] rounded-[4px] border border-line bg-[var(--color-mono-bg)]"
          aria-label="Photo placeholder"
        >
          <div class="flex h-full items-center justify-center font-mono text-xs text-ink/40">
            photo coming
          </div>
        </div>
        <dl class="space-y-3 font-mono text-xs text-ink/80">
          <div>
            <dt class="text-ink/50">Based in</dt>
            <dd>Wellington, NZ</dd>
          </div>
          <div>
            <dt class="text-ink/50">Languages</dt>
            <dd>English · 中文 (native)</dd>
          </div>
          <div>
            <dt class="text-ink/50">Previously</dt>
            <dd>QA engineer, fintech &amp; ecommerce</dd>
          </div>
        </dl>
      </aside>

      <div class="space-y-8 text-ink/85">
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-ink sm:text-2xl">From QA to building things that ship.</h2>
          <p class="mt-3">
            I spent years finding bugs other people built. Broken checkout flows, forms that silently
            ate submissions, mobile pages that scrolled sideways. The pattern is always the same — somebody
            built it, somebody else shipped it, and nobody ran it on a real phone.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-3">
            I started this studio so local businesses can buy a site that doesn't ship like that.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-ink sm:text-2xl">Why this, why now.</h2>
          <p class="mt-3">
            Wellington has a lot of small businesses with $5,000 quotes from agencies they can't justify,
            sitting beside $99 template sites that look it. There's a missing middle: thoughtful, fast,
            tested sites at a price a sole trader can sign off in an afternoon.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-3">
            That's the gap I'm filling. Three builds a month, full attention each, fixed prices.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-ink sm:text-2xl">Bilingual — and I mean it.</h2>
          <p class="mt-3">
            I grew up speaking Mandarin at home and English everywhere else. When I deliver a bilingual site,
            both languages are written, not translated. A direct translation of Kiwi small-business English
            reads stiff and foreign to a Chinese customer — and you lose the trust you were trying to build.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-ink sm:text-2xl">How I work.</h2>
          <ul class="mt-3 space-y-2">
            <li class="flex items-baseline gap-2">
              <span class="font-mono text-pass">✓</span>
              <span>Fixed price agreed up front. No "scope creep" invoices.</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-baseline gap-2">
              <span class="font-mono text-pass">✓</span>
              <span>Daily check-ins on a staging URL. You see progress; I don't disappear.</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-baseline gap-2">
              <span class="font-mono text-pass">✓</span>
              <span>You own the code, the domain, and the hosting from day one.</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-baseline gap-2">
              <span class="font-mono text-pass">✓</span>
              <span>If automated tests fail, I don't deploy. Same standard I held vendors to in QA.</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3 pt-2">
          <Button href="/contact" variant="primary">Start a project</Button>
          <Button href="/packages" variant="secondary">See packages</Button>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
